newsitem.title: UK: IPE gas oil ends weaker, down with NYMEX heating o.
newsitem.headline: IPE gas oil ends weaker, down with NYMEX heating o.

text.p: IPE gas oil ended down on Wednesday, dragged lower by NYMEX heating oil which saw some liquidation following bearish overnight API statistics.
December Brent crude hit the day's lows after breaking down through long-erm uptrend which activated some sell stops, brokers said.

November gas oil closed down $5 at $225.75 a tonne with some good fund selling seen in the last hour of trade. After the gas oil close, December Brent broke below the $24.14 uptrend and dipped to a low of $24.02 a barrel.
The contract traded at 1644 GMT down 64 cents at $24.02.

Liquidation on NYMEX heating oil following the overnight API U.S. weekly stock figures which showed a bearish build of 2.47 million barrels in the Northeast U.S. was the main reason for the fall, traders said.
